[tb_start_text mode=3]
Yuu has always been by my side since then.[l][r]
She always smiles beside me when I wake up.[l][r]
She shows me various things I can eat and feeds me.[l][r]
[r]Where she buys those things, if the money is enough,[r]
what about school... I do wonder.[l][r]

[r]...I can't bring myself to ask.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm]
[tb_start_text mode=3]
Yuu is kind.[l][r]
Yuu is warm.[l][r]
Yuu is soft.[l][r]
Yuu is comfortable.[l][r]
Yuu. Yuu-chan. Yuri...[l][r]
I want to savor that feeling over and over again. My very own... Yuri.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm]
[bg time="1500" method="crossfade" storage="rom7.jpg"]
[tb_start_text mode=3]
She doesn't belong to anyone. I know she doesn't truly belong to me either.[l][r]
But I can't let go anymore. Opening my hand or turning my eyes away is scary.[l][r]
I cling to Yuu like a small child clings to their mother on a train, full of fear and affection.[l][r]
Yesterday or today, Yuu was looking out the window. When I asked if she was curious about the outside, she shook her head no.[l][r]
Yuu closed the curtains, looked at me, and smiled, saying it's nothing. The flat light of the ceiling lamp lit up her hair like a doll's.[l][r]
I thought it was beautiful.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm]
[tb_start_text mode=3]
Forget about the world outside. Because,[l][r]
[r]we already have such a beautiful world here.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

