[tb_start_text mode=3]
Look at the window, the glass, the mirror.[r]
See my reflection.[l][r]
Since deciding to stay with Chi-chan forever, the person in the mirror looks really happy.[l][r]
She doesn't talk or laugh on her own. Just looks happy.[l][r]
[r]That's fine with me.[l][r]
And that's... all that matters.[l][r]
I'll close the curtains and only look at Chi-chan.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm]
[tb_start_text mode=3]
Chi-chan eats the food I prepare for her.[l][r]
Chi-chan apologizes when she throws up.[l][r]
She remembers the memories of the other world and talks nostalgically.[l][r]
[r]She says she loves me, and only me.[l][r]
[r]My very own... Chi-to.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm]
[tb_start_text mode=3]
But deep down, I know the truth.[l][r]
Even if I close the curtains or hide the mirror, I can still see it. I can see myself reflected in Chi-chan's eyes.[l][r]
[r]That's why I realize,[l][r]
the happy face I see in her eyes is a facade.[l][r]

[r]But you know.[r]
Even so, it's okay now.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

